# {{ projectName }}

DARE-shaped Rust API on Axum 0.7. Layered Design: Handler → Service → Repository → Model.

## Setup

```bash
cp .env.example .env
docker compose up -d postgres
cargo install sqlx-cli --no-default-features --features postgres
sqlx database create
sqlx migrate run
cargo run
```

## Commands

- `cargo run` — dev server (port 8000)
- `cargo test --workspace` — tests
- `cargo clippy -- -D warnings` — lint (warnings are errors)
- `cargo audit` — RustSec advisory audit
- `sqlx migrate add <name>` — new migration
- `sqlx migrate run` — apply migrations

## Endpoints

| Method | Path | Auth | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| POST | `/auth/login` | none | Exchange email+password for JWT |
| GET | `/auth/me` | Bearer | Current user info |
| GET | `/users` | Bearer | List users (query: page, limit) |
| POST | `/users` | Bearer (admin) | Create user |
| GET | `/ws` | upgrade | WebSocket echo example |
| GET | `/openapi.json` | none | OpenAPI 3.x document (utoipa-generated at runtime) |
| GET | `/swagger-ui` | none | Swagger UI |

## Layered Design

- `src/handlers/` — Axum extractors and route handlers
- `src/services/` — business logic
- `src/repositories/` — sqlx queries
- `src/models/` — domain structs (FromRow / Serialize)
- `src/middleware/` — auth + rate limit
- `src/llm/` — provider abstraction

Handlers never call sqlx directly — they go through services → repositories.

## Env vars

See `.env.example`. Required: `DATABASE_URL`, `JWT_SECRET`.

